---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Wolf Stove Repair | Southern California | Dual Fuel, Pro Sealed Burners";
const description = "Wolf stove repair across Southern California — Dual Fuel DF / Pro Gas GR / Induction / L / M series. Sub-Zero Group Madison WI. Same-day, $89 diagnostic. (424) 325-0520.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/wolf-stove-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is Wolf the same company as Viking?",
    a: "No — different companies in the pro-grade residential stove market. <b>Wolf</b> is part of Sub-Zero Group Inc., the independent Madison, Wisconsin-based company (Sub-Zero Group operates three brands: Sub-Zero refrigeration, Wolf cooking, Cove dishwashers — all under the same parent since the Sub-Zero acquisition of Wolf in 2000). <b>Viking</b> is a separate company based in Greenwood, Mississippi, owned by Middleby Corporation since 2013. Both are luxury-tier residential stove brands with overlapping market positioning, but the platforms, parts networks, service paths, and corporate ownership are entirely distinct. Our techs approach Wolf and Viking as separate diagnostic categories with separate parts-inventory rotations. Also worth flagging: <b>Wolf Residential (Sub-Zero Group) ≠ Wolf Commercial (ITW Food Equipment Group)</b> — different companies entirely. If a customer mentions commercial Wolf, that's not us."
  },
  {
    q: "What Wolf stove models are most common in LA?",
    a: "Wolf Dual Fuel (DF) series dominates LA Wolf stove installs. DF30 (30-inch dual-fuel range-stove), DF36 (36-inch), DF48 (48-inch), and DF60 (60-inch) ship into Bel Air / Beverly Hills / Pacific Palisades / Hollywood Hills custom kitchens as the default Wolf spec. Dual Fuel means gas cooktop + electric convection oven — Wolf's signature architecture combining gas cooking control with electric convection precision. Pro Gas (GR) series is the second-most-common: GR30 / GR36 / GR48 professional all-gas stoves with Wolf's 20,000 BTU dual-stacked sealed burners. Induction (I) series at 36\" and 48\" for kitchens specifying induction cooktop over gas. L series is Wolf's entry-level dual-fuel. M series adds steam convection on some models. Our LA installed base concentrates Dual Fuel + Pro Gas in roughly 70-30 split of service volume."
  },
  {
    q: "Our Wolf Pro burner won't spark — what's the usual cause?",
    a: "Wolf Pro sealed burners at 20,000 BTU dual-stacked have specific spark-module + burner architecture. Diagnostic order: (1) spark-module ignition — electronic ignitor doesn't click when you turn the burner knob; Wolf-specific spark-module swap $260–$380; (2) burner cap seating — dual-stacked cap not fully seated produces inconsistent spark contact; reseating $89 diagnostic; (3) air-mixture adjustment — Wolf Pro burners have adjustable air-fuel mixture that drifts over years; adjustment $140–$240; (4) ignitor-wire harness continuity — Wolf Pro wire harnesses are specialty parts; $180–$280; (5) gas valve or regulator — rare, Wolf valves are engineered for longer service life than mainstream brands; swap $340–$520 when needed. Our techs carry Wolf spark-module parts in dispatch for the most common service scenarios. Sub-Zero Group parts from Madison WI typically 3-5 day lead on common items."
  },
  {
    q: "Wolf Dual Fuel — is the gas cooktop + electric oven combination actually better?",
    a: "Honest field read: yes for specific cooking styles, but the Dual Fuel configuration has distinct service complexity. Gas cooktop delivers immediate heat response + visual flame control that electric induction can't match — preferred for serious cooking. Electric convection oven provides more precise temperature control + better browning consistency than gas ovens — preferred for baking + roasting. Dual Fuel pairs both strengths. Service complexity: Dual Fuel architecture uses two separate control boards (cooktop-side + oven-side) with inter-board communication protocols. Failures affect either side independently, and the board-communication diagnostic requires Wolf-specific technical knowledge. Pro Gas all-gas configuration is simpler service-wise (single gas system) but lacks the electric oven precision. For LA custom kitchens where the cooking aesthetic + performance matters, Dual Fuel is usually the right Wolf spec despite slightly higher service economics."
  },
  {
    q: "How does Wolf's Sub-Zero Group service network reach LA?",
    a: "Sub-Zero Group's Madison WI headquarters ships Wolf parts through an established authorized service network with LA coverage. Typical parts lead times: common service items (spark modules, burner components, control-board modules, oven elements) 3-5 days from Madison distribution to LA authorized service. Specialty items (Wolf-specific 20k BTU burner assemblies, Dual Fuel dual-control boards, M-series steam components) run 5-10 days. For in-warranty Wolf service, the Sub-Zero Group factory-authorized path is the right choice — preserves warranty rights + gives access to Wolf-specific technical support. Out-of-warranty Wolf service, we handle directly with Sub-Zero Group parts channel. Pricing runs 20-30% above mainstream-brand stove service reflecting the premium parts + specialty diagnostic requirement. Related: <a href='/brands/cove-dishwasher-repair/'>Cove dishwasher repair</a> (Sub-Zero Group sibling) and <a href='/brands/sub-zero-refrigerator-repair/'>Sub-Zero refrigerator repair</a>."
  },
  {
    q: "What does Wolf stove repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic is $89, waived when you authorize the repair. Common Wolf stove bands: spark-module ignition $260–$380 (Wolf-specific); thermocouple / safety-hold service $220–$320; burner cap / seating service $120–$220; Pro burner air-mixture adjustment $140–$240; ignitor-wire harness $180–$280; gas valve swap $340–$520; oven igniter (Dual Fuel / Pro Gas with oven) $280–$420; temperature sensor $220–$320; convection fan motor (Dual Fuel electric oven) $320–$460; surface light switch $180–$260; cooktop-side control board $440–$640; oven-side control board $440–$640; board-to-board communication diagnostic $140–$240; full cooktop + oven control-system replacement $700–$1,000 when both sides fail simultaneously. Wolf service runs 20-30% above mainstream-brand economics reflecting premium parts + specialty service time. Sub-Zero Group Madison parts 3-5 day typical lead on common items."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — Wolf Stove Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical, "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL, "priceRange": "$$$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "serviceType": "Wolf Stove Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "Wolf stove repair across Southern California — LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. Dual Fuel DF series (DF30/DF36/DF48/DF60), Pro Gas GR series (20k BTU dual-stacked sealed burners), Induction I series, L + M series. Sub-Zero Group Inc. Madison WI, pro-grade residential luxury. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "89.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair" } }
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Wolf", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/wolf/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Wolf Stove Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">{schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}</Fragment>
  <div class="call-banner"><div class="wrap"><span>Wolf stove service? Same-day across all 5 SoCal counties:</span><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a></div></div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › Wolf › Stove Repair</div>
    <h1>Wolf Stove Repair</h1>
    <p class="lede">Wolf is Sub-Zero Group Inc.'s pro-grade residential cooking brand — part of the independent Madison, Wisconsin-based parent that also operates Sub-Zero refrigeration and Cove dishwashers. Wolf's residential stove lineup — Dual Fuel DF series, Pro Gas GR series, Induction I series, L entry-level, M steam-convection — ships into LA's luxury custom-kitchen segment as one of the two reference pro-grade brands (alongside Viking). The 20,000 BTU dual-stacked sealed burners on Pro Gas + Dual Fuel configurations are Wolf's signature. Our LA service concentrates in Bel Air, Beverly Hills, Pacific Palisades, Hollywood Hills, Manhattan Beach, Pasadena — the luxury-kitchen concentration where Wolf installs dominate. Sub-Zero Group Madison parts network delivers 3-5 day typical lead on common service items. Same-day dispatch, $89 residential diagnostic waived with the repair.</p>
    <div class="hero-cta"><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div>
    <ul class="hero-facts">
      <li><b>Sub-Zero Group Madison WI</b> — same parent as Sub-Zero + Cove</li>
      <li><b>Dual Fuel DF + Pro Gas GR signature</b> — 20,000 BTU dual-stacked sealed burners</li>
      <li><b>LA luxury-kitchen concentration</b> — Bel Air / Beverly Hills / Pacific Palisades</li>
      <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b> — waived when you authorize the repair</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span><span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span><span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Wolf in LA — pro-grade residential luxury, Sub-Zero Group heritage</h2>
    <p>Wolf's US luxury-stove positioning is anchored in pro-grade residential engineering — the 20,000 BTU dual-stacked sealed burners deliver commercial-kitchen heat output in residential-spec packages. Sub-Zero Group's 2000 acquisition of Wolf integrated the brand into the three-brand Madison family (Sub-Zero refrigeration + Wolf cooking + Cove dishwashers, all under coordinated-kitchen-suite positioning). For LA, Wolf is one of the two reference luxury stove choices alongside Viking — the selection typically comes down to Dual Fuel preference (Wolf) vs. Viking's heritage all-gas positioning.</p>
    <p>LA Wolf stove service concentrates in the highest-luxury kitchen geographies: Bel Air + Beverly Hills + Holmby Hills major custom remodels; Pacific Palisades canyon estates; Hollywood Hills architecturally-significant homes; Manhattan Beach coastal luxury; Pasadena + San Marino established premium; Encino + Calabasas Valley estates; Newport Coast + Corona del Mar OC luxury. Wolf installs typically ship alongside Sub-Zero refrigeration and Cove dishwashers in coordinated Sub-Zero Group kitchen suites — our service approach respects the coordinated-suite integration during service.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Wolf stove failures our techs see most often</h2>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Spark-module ignition (Pro burners)</h3><p>Wolf-specific spark modules fail at 7-10 years daily-use. Swap $260–$380.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Dual Fuel dual-control board communication</h3><p>Cooktop-side + oven-side boards communicate via inter-board protocol. Communication fault $140–$240 diagnostic; board swap $440–$640 per side if fault confirmed.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Convection fan motor (Dual Fuel electric oven)</h3><p>Motor swap $320–$460 on convection-oven-side of Dual Fuel configurations.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Pro burner air-mixture + burner cap</h3><p>Adjustment $140–$240; cap replacement $120–$220 when damaged.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Ignitor-wire harness</h3><p>Wolf specialty harness $180–$280 when continuity fault confirmed.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Gas valve + regulator (rare)</h3><p>Swap $340–$520. Wolf valves are engineered for long service life; failure uncommon before 15+ years.</p></div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Wolf stove product lines we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Dual Fuel DF series (signature)</h3><p>DF30, DF36, DF48, DF60. Gas cooktop + electric convection oven. LA Wolf volume platform.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Pro Gas GR series</h3><p>GR30, GR36, GR48. 20,000 BTU dual-stacked sealed burners. All-gas professional.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Induction I series</h3><p>I36, I48. Induction cooktop configurations for all-electric or induction-preference kitchens.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>L series entry-level Dual Fuel</h3><p>Dual-fuel architecture at lower-trim pricing than DF volume series.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>M steam-convection</h3><p>Higher-trim steam convection ovens integrated into select stove configurations.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Sub-Zero Group coordinated service</h3><p>Madison WI parts distribution shared across Sub-Zero + Wolf + Cove sister brands.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Wolf vs Viking vs Thermador — luxury stove buyer matrix</h2>
    <p>Three luxury residential stove brands dominate LA premium kitchens, each with distinct platform + service implications.</p>
    <p><b>Wolf</b> — this page. Sub-Zero Group Madison WI, Dual Fuel DF signature, 20k BTU dual-stacked Pro burners, Sub-Zero Group coordinated kitchen-suite integration.</p>
    <p><b>Viking</b> — Greenwood MS, Middleby-owned, heritage all-gas pro-grade, 23k BTU Professional Sealed burners. See <a href="/brands/viking-stove-repair/">Viking stove repair</a>.</p>
    <p><b>Thermador</b> — BSH (Bosch Siemens Hausgeräte), German-engineered, Irvine CA parts warehouse (LA-local advantage), Pro Harmony + Pro Grand + Star Burner signature. See <a href="/brands/thermador-stove-repair/">Thermador stove repair</a>.</p>
    <p>Choice drivers: Wolf for Dual Fuel pragmatism + Sub-Zero Group suite integration; Viking for heritage all-gas + Professional burner performance; Thermador for BSH German-engineering + Irvine parts proximity. All three at similar premium pricing and service-economics tiers. Our techs handle all three with platform-specific diagnostic knowledge.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>What Wolf stove repair typically costs</h2>
    <table class="price-table">
      <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Waived with repair</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Spark-module ignition</td><td>$260 – $380</td><td>Wolf-specific</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Thermocouple / safety-hold</td><td>$220 – $320</td><td>Gas-side fault</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Burner cap / seating</td><td>$120 – $220</td><td>Dual-stacked cap</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Pro burner air-mixture</td><td>$140 – $240</td><td>Adjustment service</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Ignitor-wire harness</td><td>$180 – $280</td><td>Continuity fault</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Gas valve swap</td><td>$340 – $520</td><td>Rare 15+ year service</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Oven igniter</td><td>$280 – $420</td><td>Dual Fuel / Pro Gas oven</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Temperature sensor</td><td>$220 – $320</td><td>Oven-side fault</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Convection fan motor</td><td>$320 – $460</td><td>Dual Fuel electric oven</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Cooktop-side control board</td><td>$440 – $640</td><td>Dual Fuel dual-board</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Oven-side control board</td><td>$440 – $640</td><td>Dual Fuel dual-board</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Board-to-board comm diagnostic</td><td>$140 – $240</td><td>Inter-board protocol</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Full cooktop + oven board swap</td><td>$700 – $1,000</td><td>Both boards simultaneously</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p class="small">Related: <a href="/brands/wolf-range-repair/">Wolf range repair</a> · <a href="/brands/wolf-cooktop-repair/">Wolf cooktop repair</a> · <a href="/brands/wolf-oven-repair/">Wolf oven repair</a> · <a href="/brands/sub-zero-refrigerator-repair/">Sub-Zero refrigerator repair</a> · <a href="/brands/cove-dishwasher-repair/">Cove dishwasher repair</a>.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Service areas — where our Wolf stove calls come from</h2>
    <div class="area-grid">
      <div><h4>Bel Air + Beverly Hills + Holmby Hills</h4><p><a href="/beverly-hills/">Beverly Hills</a> · Bel Air · Holmby Hills · Trousdale</p></div>
      <div><h4>Pacific Palisades + Brentwood</h4><p>Pacific Palisades · Brentwood · Rustic Canyon</p></div>
      <div><h4>Hollywood Hills architectural</h4><p>Hollywood Hills · Laurel Canyon · Outpost Estates · Mount Olympus</p></div>
      <div><h4>Manhattan Beach + coastal luxury</h4><p>Manhattan Beach · Palos Verdes · <a href="/malibu/">Malibu</a></p></div>
